    en: "Medicaid Home and Community-Based Services (HCBS) waivers, authorized under federal 42 USC 1396n(c) and 1396n(k), let states cover in-home, community-based services that Medicaid would not otherwise pay for — helping people with disabilities, developmental disabilities, traumatic brain injuries, and chronic illness remain in the community instead of institutional settings. New York operates multiple waiver programs: OPWDD HCBS Waiver (developmental disabilities), Nursing Home Transition and Diversion (NHTD), Traumatic Brain Injury (TBI), and Children's Waiver. Each has specific eligibility, services, and enrollment windows. The NY Medicaid Managed Long-Term Care (MLTC) program serves seniors needing community-based long-term care. Waiver services typically include personal care, home modifications, respite, assistive technology, and specialized therapies."
